programme.desc: PRS investigates a case involving single mom, Dawn, and her 5-year-old daughter, both of whom are tormented by the appearance of a hag they call "lady vampire."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Return of the Dead: Glove II
programme.desc: PRS returns to the site of one of their most famous cases, Daisytown, PA, where they had discovered a glove print of an old miner that they determined was the spirit of a Great-Grandfather.
programme.sub-title: Return of the Dead: Glove II

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Homecoming
programme.desc: Ryan brings PRS to his hometown of Sumter, SC to investigate a chilling case where a young boy was tragically shot and killed on a front doorstep while trick-or-treating on Halloween.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Mothman
programme.desc: Ryan takes his team to Point Pleasant, West Virginia to investigate his own personal holy grail of paranormal lore: the mysterious Mothman.

programme.title: Paranormal State: First Contact
programme.desc: Washington State, a hotbed of unexplained paranormal activity. Between possible UFOs in the sky and winged creatures in the woods, Ryan and his team are forced to face their fears and deal with the question: Are we truly alone in the universe?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Newton House - Part 1
programme.desc: Yvette and the team are joined by the members of Bridgend metal band Bullet for My Valentine as they investigate Newton House, Llandeilo.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Newton House - Part 2
programme.desc: The team and special guests Bullet for My Valentine continue their investigation of Newton House. Including footage of an old wheelchair apparently moving by itself.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Galleries of Justice
programme.desc: The team is joined by the sister of regular member Mel Crump as they visit the Galleries of Justice in Nottingham. Yvette is followed by a smelly spirit.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Delapre Abbey
programme.desc: Five members of the Northampton Saints rugby team join the Most Haunted team to investigate Delapre Abbey in Northampton. Ghostly nuns have been reported here.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The National Emergency Service Museum, Sheffield
programme.desc: The Most Haunted team visits a collection of emergency services vehicles in Sheffield. Will they make contact with the legendary evil spirit of Caine?
programme.sub-title: The National Emergency Service Museum, Sheffield

programme.title: Most Haunted: Ye Olde King's Head, Chester
programme.desc: The team visits the historic city of Chester to investigate what is reported to be one of the most haunted pubs in England. Thirteen spirits are said to reside here.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Drakelow Tunnels
programme.desc: The team investigates the tunnels beneath Drakelow Hill in Worcestershire that once housed a WWII factory and then a Cold War command complex.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: One Fresh Batch of Lemonade - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan enlists the aid of a gymnast to rehabilitate Deke. Meanwhile, Deke's parents have been deeply affected by the accident.
programme.sub-title: One Fresh Batch of Lemonade - Part 2

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Divine Madness
programme.desc: A construction company tycoon now believes he's King Arthur, and his estranged son determines to have him declared incompetent. Can Jonathan work a reconciliation?

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Catch A Falling Star
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark have been hired to look after the kids of a movie star who never has time to spend with his family.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Help Wanted: Angel
programme.desc: An elderly scriptwriter needs someone to bankroll his movie. Meanwhile, Mark has fallen in love with an attractive woman, but Jonathan receives news about her from higher up.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Dust Child
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark must help an Amerasian girl facing racial prejudice when she goes to live with her father's family in the United States.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Hotel Of Dreams
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are bellhops at a hotel that has been given to an aimless young man by his father. They must deal with an unkind boss, an obnoxious kid and a difficult guest.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Another Song For Christmas
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark try to help a heartless used car salesman reconsider his actions on Christmas Eve.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Rotchell
programme.desc: Essex girl Debbie Rotchell, 49, smokes 15,000 cigarettes a year and loves to sunbathe. Debbie gets a wake-up call when a poll of one hundred people puts her at 55. Just as well Nicky Hambleton-Jones is on hand with her time-fighting trio.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Military Makeover
programme.desc: As former Marine, Kimberly wasn't "trained" in the art of looking feminine and as a single mother of three, now isn't the time for her to begin learning. She just doesn't have the time. Time to make Kimberly look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hairy Mary Quite Contrary
programme.desc: Mary is an overworked telecommuter and mother of twin 5-year-old girls. Since she works from home, Mary has traded in her business suits for sweats and a ponytail. We'll see if we can make Mary look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Better Days Ahead
programme.desc: Serena came to the U.S. from Cambodia at age seven and helped care for her younger siblings. She loves them, but does not love being mistaken for their mother. Serena had to grow up too fast, but she doesn't have to look like it.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Rosy Red To Peaches And Cream
programme.desc: Monica is a working mother of three whose rosacea has gotten worse with every passing year and she is tired of hearing, 'Oh, you've been out in the sun?' The team injects motivation back into Monica's life and look.
programme.sub-title: From Rosy Red To Peaches And Cream

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Faith in a New Look
programme.desc: Peggy is a single chaplain who uses her faith and people skills helping sick children in a children's hospital. She wants to regain her confidence with a younger, sassier look – that's where we come in. It's time to make Peggy look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Backstage To Center Stage
programme.desc: Mimi was a successful touring backup singer, and decided to take a final bow after getting married and having her daughter. Now that her daughter is older, she is ready to jump back on stage and needs the look to match.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Bummed Out To Belle Of The Ball
programme.desc: Jennifer has been feeling older since her back injury six months ago. Her job requires shopping in Beverly Hills and attending charity balls in appropriate attire. But at six feet tall, size 16 and on a budget, this is no easy task. She needs a makeover!
programme.sub-title: From Bummed Out To Belle Of The Ball

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Saying "I Do" To A New Look
programme.desc: Driving a big rig over two million miles and being a single dad have taken a huge toll on Michael's appearance. But major dental prosthetics and state-of-the-art dermatology bring out his softer side, then it's up to the Glam Squad to find a new look!
programme.sub-title: Saying "I Do" To A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Tony Goodwin "One Year On"
programme.desc: We revisit Midlands' band promoter Tony Goodwin who's poll of one hundred people last year suggested he was a colossal thirteen years older than he actually was.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Mom's Day Out
programme.desc: Nancy is a mother who's almost out of gas and in need of a rejuvenating jump-start. The glam squad breathes life into Nancy's fashion sense and provides this over-worked parent some relief from her frazzled life.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jayne English
programme.desc: Can Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her illustrious team of experts turn back time for 41-year-old Jayne English who went from a size 22 to a size 10 in just 18 months?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Nerys McGarry
programme.desc: Can the team pull off their biggest challenge to date and make Nerys McGarry - who has lost eight stone - 21 years younger?

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: In his role as State Vet, Danny works with wealthy conservationist, Anton Ziegler, to catch a group of leopard hunters. Ziegler is also buying a tiger from Vanessa, who struggling with her finances, desperately needs the money to ensure Mara's future.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Du Plessis has started a one man campaign of vandalism against the new neighbours at Mara; Peeters and the mining company. When Peeters catches him on CCTV, Du Plessis is fined and given a restraining order to keep him away from Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Du Plessis comes to meet Caroline's plane but he doesn't seem happy – he has seen that the mining company have already started building the road which threatens Leopard's Den.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: The family are making arrangements to leave Leopard's Den, all except Du Plessis who is steadfastly refusing to accept that he has lost his home. He won't use his share of the money from the sale of the land to buy somewhere else.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: The family have been squatting at Leopard's Den as they prepare to make their last stand to prevent the bulldozers from destroying their home. Du Plessis and Fatani bring elephants and a giraffe to dissuade the construction crew from moving in.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: After the devastating loss of Leopard's Den, the family are split across continents. Caroline, Liv and a heavily pregnant Alice are in the UK, while Danny and Du Plessis have remained in South Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny returns to South Africa with Caroline, Liv and Charlotte. They are all excited to be back and are looking forward to seeing their new home, Clearwater Farm.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: The team have received a status 2 callout; Mark Lorimer was knocked out and has multiple injuries after being hit head-on by another vehicle.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The team are called to a road accident where a woman has been cut from inside of her wrecked car.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: The team is responding to a life-threatening emergency. A cyclist in his 60s, Terrence Williams, is unresponsive and critical after an accident 15 minutes flying time from Auckland, near the small settlement of Maramarua.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The team are called out to a status 2 emergency; Clark Chamberlain was abseiling when he fell from the top of a cliff to the ground. He's now in a critical condition suffering from multiple injuries.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: The team are responding to reports of a life-or death emergency; Jim Te Whata has been pulled from the water cold, unconscious and not breathing.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggles to save two young men who are feared drowned at Hahei; a Coromandel motorcyclist is struggling with punctured lungs, and young man is trapped inside a car after a high speed accident.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Bike stunts
programme.desc: This time the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept deal with motorbike stunts: high jumps, risky drops and dangerous crashes. As usual, stunt coordinator Domi requires his motorbike specialists Daniel and Marcel to be in top form.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Ambulance
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are always looking for new spectacular stunts and are not running out of options. Stunt coordinator Domi’s latest idea involves an old ambulance.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Matrix
programme.desc: Martial arts specialist Ramazan creates a choreography for a fight. It involves four stuntmen who need to disguise as secret agents and bash on him. Will Ramazan be able to free himself from this uncomfortable position?

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Multiple Collision
programme.desc: Fog, darkness and a pileup involving multiple cars: It's a scene that you can often see on highways and it's a scene that the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept want to recreate as part of a stunt with burning people.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The White Army
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept leave their headquarters behind and travel to a ski resort. Between the trees of a nearby forest they simulate the attack of an army of white-dressed soldiers.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Alarm in the Ski Resort
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are still at their ski resort and party hard. This time they prepared a spectacular stunt involving a station wagon. It is thrown 50 meters into the air with a cannon.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Body Stunt Highlights
programme.desc: Today it's Action Concepts most popular and most spectacular body stunts: Jumping from rooftops, falling of a driving car, tumbling down stairs. Despite inevitable wounds, the legendary stunt crew enjoys the job.

programme.title: Supercars: 40 Years of BMW M
programme.desc: Supercars celebrates the unbelievable success of the BMW M Ltd. It all began in 1972 with the M1, one of the style icons of the supercars.

programme.title: Supercars: James Bond Special
programme.desc: 1962 saw the release of the first ever James Bond film “Dr. No”. In celebration of the 50th big screen anniversary Supercars shows the most popular, fastest and most beautiful cars from the 007 franchise.

programme.title: Supercars: Asian Bestsellers
programme.desc: They come from another world. A world in which their abbreviations are enough to bring about an earthquake. Lexus IS-F, Nissan GTR, the Juke R and the Infiniti FX 50 are all exotic models.

programme.title: Supercars: Lamborghini
programme.desc: On this episode of Supercars, men's inner strength comes alive. Sant Agata Bolognese, the home of Lamborghini, is the ideal place to take the Gallardo models out for a spin. Plus: the fastest city tour in the world.

programme.title: Supercars: Best of 2012
programme.desc: On this episode of Supercars, Patrick Simon takes the opportunity to look back at some of his personal automotive highlights. As a race driver, he tested some of the greatest, fastest and most expensive super sports cars.

programme.title: Supercars: Porsche to the Max!
programme.desc: 2011 has been a record year for Porsche. The German car manufacturer was able to sell more cars than ever before. But it is not just Porsche that is popular with sports car fans, Porsche refiners enjoy success, too.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Dark Matter
programme.desc: When the mother ship hits dark matter, the ship dos not begin to heal itself. Zo'or is left in an unconscious state and Sandoval takes control. He decides it is time to liberate the Earth from the Taelons.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Keys to the Kingdom
programme.desc: The relic left by Ma'el is stolen from the mother ship. Zo'or threatens to destroy a major city if it isn't returned. Liam believes the final chapters contain information on synthesizing core energy.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Street Chase
programme.desc: Sandoval is watching via nanobots inside Street as she tries to decipher Ma'el's riddle. She tries to figure out how to escape from Sandoval and the Taelons forcing her to solve the riddle. She flashes back to childhood fears.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Trapped by Time
programme.desc: Liam and Renee learn of a facility where time travelers from the future are being held. They try to learn from them what happens to the Taelons. Sandoval's wife is used as a pawn to gain important information from him.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Atonement
programme.desc: Sandoval goes to Renee to request a trial to testify to atrocities against humanity committed by the Taelons. A manhunt for Sandoval begins when he quits and leaves the mother ship. Liam has to protect him on his way to the grand jury.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Blood Ties
programme.desc: Strange assaults and several deaths may be related to a Doors/Taelon joint venture where Taelon core energy was used to heal people. It appears that the energy is being sucked back out of the patients.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Hearts and Minds
programme.desc: When Renee's boyfriend appears to her while he is imprisoned on the mother ship, Liam theorizes a special energy bond between the pair. Zo'or is upset by the human's betrayal and bans all humans from the mother ship.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Epiphany
programme.desc: The Taelons announce that they will all go into death stasis and wait on the mother ship for humans to discover how to create core energy and revive them. Zo'or and Da'an don't trust each other to be the last to submit to stasis.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Dark Horizons
programme.desc: Eight Taelons are killed when protectors' implants are re-calibrated with a new imperative to kill instead of protect Taelons. They fear the Jiridians have found a way to control the CVIs. Meanwhile, their core energy continues to deplete.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hope for the Best
programme.desc: Hope is a dedicated single parent who has been told she dresses too old for her age. Along with the daily stresses of work and motherhood, the recent loss of Hope's mother's has also taken its toll on her appearance.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Danny is in prison, accused of murdering Peeters, but Du Plessis is determined to prove his friend's innocence by any means he can. Du Plessis' first attempt backfires disastrously when he harangues a police officer and ends up in a cell next to Danny.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: With Danny away, and Du Plessis undertaking an ignominious stretch of community service, Ed is left in charge of running the Endangered Species Project.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Ed are anxiously preparing for a review with JLW, the pharmaceutical company that fund their Endangered Species Project. They are desperate for it to go smoothly, and as a result are driving the rest of the family mad.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Following the loss of their funding, the family are in dire financial straits. Danny and Ed attempt to get an extension on their mortgage but are refused. Fiona spurs Ed on, telling him that the man she used to know would have a plan for survival.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Strange things are happening at Leopard's Den. The family awake to find frogs everywhere, seemingly having rained down overnight; the giraffe refuses to budge from the front gate and the cheetah is off its food.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggles to save two young men who are feared drowned at Hahei; a Coromandel motorcyclist is struggling with punctured lungs, and young man is trapped inside a car after a high speed accident.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: A teenage motorcyclist is fighting for his life after crashing on a remote farm near Warkworth, a man has 2nd degree burns to his face and hands from an accidental explosion, and four men are missing after two boats capsized on the Kawhia bar.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team battles to save a man trapped in his overturned Land Rover on Rakino Island; a star rugby player at Onewhero may have broken his neck after a scrum collapsed, and a man out cycling on Waiheke is clinging to life after a cardiac arrest.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The chopper team has an intense struggle to keep a young Waikato woman alive after her car collided with a heavy truck, an 18 year old man is in terrible pain with a dislocated shoulder, and a 9 year old boy is in a bad way after falling out of a tree.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The Westpac chopper crew attempt to save a Waiheke man who has life-threatening injuries after falling off a ladder and a motocross rider is in a bad way after a 100-foot jump goes badly wrong.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: The helicopter rescue crew responds to Pauanui to save a truck driver who's smashed through the windscreen after rolling his truck and a Port Charles family is distraught after a young girl is run over by a quad bike.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper crewmen have their hands full with five badly injured patients after a car crash near Waiuku, and a massive motorcycle pile-up leaves injured bikers all over the road, and a man may have broken his neck after falling from his horse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: As a weather bomb hits, the chopper crew set out on one of the most challenging missions they have ever undertaken 20 miles off shore, a man lays face down at Muriwai beach unable to move.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: A hang glider pilot may have broken his back after a heavy crash-landing, a Manaia man is in a bad way after coming off a sea biscuit at high speed, and a crashed Waikato driver needs an urgent air-lift to hospital to save his life.

programme.title: Supercars: Porsche to the Max!
programme.desc: 2011 has been a record year for Porsche. The German car manufacturer was able to sell more cars than ever before. But it is not just Porsche that is popular with sports car fans, Porsche refiners enjoy success, too.

programme.title: Supercars: Luxury SUVs
programme.desc: On this episode of Supercars, it’s all about luxury SUVs and off-road vehicles for the big spenders out there. What is the new Land Rover capable? Which luxury cars can we expect to see at the Grand Cherokee Summit?

programme.title: Supercars: Pagani Story
programme.desc: For petrolheads the name Pagani is a synonym of the roaring sound of thunder. This is due to the 12-cylinder high-performance engine used by the Italian sports car manufacturer to make the ground shake.

programme.title: Supercars: Hot Supercars
programme.desc: Making something perfect even better isn’t possible – or is it? Aston Martin V8 Vantage, Porsche 918 Spyder, Bentley Mulsanne, Audi R8 V10 and Bugatti Veyron Grand Sport Super Vitesse make the impossible possible.

programme.title: Supercars: German Supercars
programme.desc: They are long and heavy, and they are German: the A8 Audi does not do much downsizing as well as the large executive cars from BMW or the luxurious VW Phaeton. The big players of the premium car manufacturers!

programme.title: Supercars: Motor Show Geneva
programme.desc: There are details which set supercars apart from normal cars and these details are essential. Supercars are the biggest, loudest and most expensive cars on the highway; they're four-wheeled works of art.

programme.title: Supercars: V8 Power
programme.desc: The 'facelift' of the new Mercedes E cost around one billion euros! But it is only one part of the exclusivity of the new E 63 AMG. Of course, the high performance brand of Mercedes-Benz added several other features!

programme.title: Supercars: British Power
programme.desc: Very British: power and performance, craftsmanship and design. We have a look at the most beautiful cars of Aston Martin, Bentley and Rolls-Royce.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Fastest Cars in the World
programme.desc: In this episode, we decide what's hot and what's not in the glamorous world of cars. This time we've decided to focus on the fastest cars.
programme.sub-title: The Fastest Cars in the World

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Expensive Production Cars
programme.desc: Real luxury. The kind of cars that you only dream of. On today's Top Ten Show, we're going to expose the most expensive cars in production.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ten Slowest Cars
programme.desc: Usually, when you talk about cars, it's all about their speed and velocity. But this time we’ve decided to turn the tables and are going to show you the opposite end of the spectrum: the ten most sluggish cars.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ten Most Fuel-efficient Cars
programme.desc: Fuel prices keep going up. Oil companies are justifying this with high demands and rising oil prices. And the prices will carry-on going up. So on today's show we are showing you ten of the most fuel-efficient cars.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Unusual Cars of Modern Times
programme.desc: Day in day out, R&D departments of car manufacturers ponder over about what constitutes the perfect car. It has to be extraordinary. It has to stand out and it has to be unique.
programme.sub-title: The Most Unusual Cars of Modern Times

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Successful Cars in the 24h Race
programme.desc: The 24-hour-race at the German Nürburgring is one of the most famous and dangerous long-distance races in the world and in today's program we'll show you the cars that have won the most titles each year.
programme.sub-title: The Most Successful Cars in the 24h Race

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Affordable Hybrid Models
programme.desc: In today's show, we are going to show you the most affordable hybrid models. The trail-blazers are definitely the Japanese, who have a whole bunch of cars to offer.
